        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): treat generic 'LLM request failed' error as transient server_error",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nTreat generic 'LLM request failed' error as transient server_error for retry/fallback.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nWhen a model returns the generic error text \"LLM request failed.\", the error classification in  did not match any specific error pattern. It fell through to the default classification of null (permanent error), preventing cron retry and model fallback from engaging.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/errors.ts`: Added `raw.includes(\"LLM request failed\") → server_error` check before the timeout check, so the error is treated as transient and retryable.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: A model that returns `\"LLM request failed.\"` is now classified as `server_error` (transient) instead of null (permanent), enabling cron retry and model fallback.\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { GENERIC_ASSISTANT_ERROR_TEXT } from \"./src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/errors.ts\"; ...'\n\n=== PR #94011: LLM Request Failed to server_error ===\n\nGENERIC_ASSISTANT_ERROR_TEXT = \"LLM request failed.\"\n\nError input: \"LLM request failed.\"\n  .includes(\"LLM request failed\"): true\n\n--- Classification flow ---\n1. classifyFailoverSignal() receives raw error message\n2. Before PR: no match for LLM request failed\n   => falls through to default => null (permanent error)\n   => model cron never retries, fallback never fires\n3. After PR: raw.includes(\"LLM request failed\") is true\n   => returns toReasonClassification(\"server_error\")\n   => transient, retryable => cron retries, fallback engages\n```\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end with a live cron job hitting a model returning this error.\n\n## Risk\n\n- [x] Backwards compatible (additive check)\n- [x] Only affects retry classification\n\nCloses: #93931",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93931-model-fallbacks-never-engage",
